column3: Shape and positioning in the midfield is all over the place – hard to tell what position each midfielder is playing
Left back MIA on second goal; setup ball played into space on left flank, center back and left mid contained, but overload allowed scoring chance
Need to be more patient in possession – Xavier’s poor positioning in midfield is providing a lot of open space to attack if you can keep the ball for a couple passes and find the open areas.
Midfielders abandoning their spaces to run forward en masse
Right stood and watched the play when the guy he was supposed to be marking scored
Players out of shape, leaving large empty spaces for attack
